------------------------------------------------------------------------
Modifications made in this fork (Section 4(b) "stated changes"):
------------------------------------------------------------------------
  - MCP tool-poisoning and rug-pull scanning (`cerberus scan`), with
    tool-definition SHA-256 pinning.
  - Egress proxy (`cerberus proxy`) with opt-in MITM: HTTPS response-body
    scanning and redaction of structured secrets from the outbound prompt
    to LLM providers, plus a plaintext/non-provider credential guard.
  - Offline supply-chain dependency audit (`cerberus deps`) over lockfiles
    with an OSV.dev advisory seed (optional online query).
  - Refreshable offline IOC destination feed (`cerberus feeds`).
  - Command-chaining defense: segment-aware evaluation with de-obfuscation
    (dequote / deslash / deexpand / deansi) and a risky-path guard.
  - Expanded default policy and substantially expanded test/simulation
    coverage (unit suites, e2e, attack / red-team / malware simulations).
